\[a(p^2 - q^2) + b(p - q) = 0.\]Since $p$ and $q$ are both positive, $p^2 - q^2 = (p - q)(p + q) > 0,$ so $a(p - q) + b = 0.$  Then $a = -\frac{b}{p - q}.$

